{"questionId":"22268795","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The local traffic authority wishes to determine the probability that, in an <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>-week period, fewer than&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math> accidents occur in a week on exactly&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math> occasions. It assumes that the weekly occurrence of accidents is independent of the week in which these occur.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the appropriate model that the traffic authority should use to determine this probability.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>binomial model&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>177</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>177</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>823</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22268795","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.9b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"State the appropriate model that the traffic authority should use to determine this probability.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}